# Normalize line endings to LF on every platform.
#
# The analyzer/code-fix tests embed source snippets as raw string literals and
# compare code-fix output (and, in a few helpers, hard-coded character offsets)
# byte-for-byte. If git checks these files out with CRLF on Windows, the literals
# pick up CRLF while the fixes/offsets assume LF, so the suite fails on Windows
# only. Forcing LF in the working tree keeps the tests platform-independent.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be normalized.
*.png binary
